The number 2026 sits on the spiral at coordinate \((23,-22)\).

The eight neighboring positions are

\[
\begin{array}{ccc}
(22,-23)&(23,-23)&(24,-23)\\
(22,-22)&(23,-22)&(24,-22)\\
(22,-21)&(23,-21)&(24,-21)
\end{array}
\]

Using the standard rule for mapping a coordinate \((x,y)\) to its number in the spiral:

* Let \(m=\max(|x|,|y|)\) and  
  \(M=(2m+1)^2\) (the maximum number on that layer).
* If \(y=-m\) (bottom side)窶ソ(n=M-(m-x)\).
* If \(x=-m\) (left side)窶ソ(n=M-(2m+(y+m))\).
* If \(y=m\) (top side)窶ソ(n=M-(4m+(x+m))\).
* If \(x=m\) (right side, except the bottom corner)窶ソ(n=M-(6m+(m-y))\).

